Quote: Much of the land in Canterbury is all freehold, but the land held by lease is generally protected by the owners buying up the river frontages. So that the Cockatoos cannot get water, I believe there is a sort of fight going on here just the same as there was in Victoria during the `65 Land Act' between squatters and cockatoos.
Notes: 1873 Feb 2 G.M.Wilson Diary in 1973 Wierzbicka Wilson Family 164

Date: 0/0/1877
Source: Journey in NZ
Author: BROOMHALL
Vol / Page: 41
Edition:
Quote:  The term squatter is well known but it is not polite to use it; and the squatter now-a-days is a settler. The man who farms less than 100 acres is a ground parrot; more than 100 acres but less than 1000 acres, he is a cockatoo; over 1000 acres,a gentleman.
